WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.133 --> 00:00:08.944
<i>Hi. this is Robbie Robertson calling.</i>

2
00:00:08.968 --> 00:00:11.113
<i>Mr. Robertson.
you're never getting your old job back.</i>

3
00:00:11.137 --> 00:00:12.906
I'm onto something truly sensational!

4
00:00:12.930 --> 00:00:17.828
<i>Three POWs from the same camp
with super abilities isn't a coincidence.</i>

5
00:00:17.852 --> 00:00:20.580
<i>The only thing
Silvermane gets off on is power.</i>

6
00:00:20.604 --> 00:00:21.604
If he gave it to me...

7
00:00:22.314 --> 00:00:23.625
<i>then he can take it all away.</i>

8
00:00:23.649 --> 00:00:25.335
They did something
to you all. didn't they?

9
00:00:25.359 --> 00:00:28.422
All I know is that once it starts.
it gets worse fast.

10
00:00:28.446 --> 00:00:30.257
But you should talk to Doc Faber.

11
00:00:30.281 --> 00:00:32.509
She can explain what's going on
a whole lot better than I can.

12
00:00:32.533 --> 00:00:34.970
<i>One of those super freaks
is tearing up the Diamond District.</i>

13
00:00:34.994 --> 00:00:36.369
<i>The Spider is there.</i>

14
00:00:37.997 --> 00:00:39.581
Who the hell is this guy?

15
00:00:43.043 --> 00:00:45.397
- Me and The Spider have teamed up...
- Not-not a team.

16
00:00:45.421 --> 00:00:47.816
- To save this city!
- Not a team. No. not a team.

17
00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:51.653
Every four years.
I decide who sits in your chair.

18
00:00:51.677 --> 00:00:53.429
I'm not backing down.

19
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:03.397
Nice to meet you. Mr. Spider.

20
00:01:21.791 --> 00:01:23.625
Hey.

21
00:01:25.878 --> 00:01:28.755
Hey. lady. what's your hurry?

22
00:01:39.141 --> 00:01:40.934
After you.

23
00:01:45.606 --> 00:01:46.982
So...

24
00:01:48.067 --> 00:01:49.461
So. yourself.

25
00:01:49.485 --> 00:01:51.546
We're about to turn over the pies.

26
00:01:51.570 --> 00:01:53.924
This one's on the house.

27
00:01:53.948 --> 00:01:56.116
What. more of a blueberry guy?

28
00:01:56.700 --> 00:02:00.222
No. there's just not a lot of free stuff
going around these days.

29
00:02:00.246 --> 00:02:01.556
Thank you.

30
00:02:01.580 --> 00:02:02.998
Very kind.

31
00:02:05.876 --> 00:02:08.045
I'm waiting. you know.

32
00:02:08.629 --> 00:02:10.982
You already know how it ends.

33
00:02:11.006 --> 00:02:14.093
Well. then start from the beginning.

34
00:02:18.722 --> 00:02:22.935
<i>We were sent to liberate
a small town in Eastern France.</i>

35
00:02:23.435 --> 00:02:26.521
<i>The Germans weren't so keen
on giving it up.</i>

36
00:02:37.366 --> 00:02:38.366
Move. move. move!

37
00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:43.747
<i>Scheiße.</i>

38
00:02:45.124 --> 00:02:46.624
Charge!

39
00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:36.675
Jones. Jones!

40
00:03:37.259 --> 00:03:38.778
Get 'em out!

41
00:03:38.802 --> 00:03:39.988
- Get 'em out.
- Please.

42
00:03:40.012 --> 00:03:41.889
- Private. follow me.
- Yes. sir.

43
00:03:42.556 --> 00:03:43.992
Move.

44
00:03:44.016 --> 00:03:45.076
Let's go.

45
00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:47.412
<i>If I was the one who had been shot.</i>

46
00:03:47.436 --> 00:03:49.372
and I almost was.

47
00:03:49.396 --> 00:03:53.001
none of this would have happened to me.

48
00:03:53.025 --> 00:03:54.943
I think about that a lot.

49
00:04:06.038 --> 00:04:09.416
<i>Private Smith and I pressed deeper
into the compound.</i>

50
00:04:14.129 --> 00:04:15.440
Jesus.

51
00:04:15.464 --> 00:04:16.775
Let's get 'em out of here.

52
00:04:16.799 --> 00:04:17.800
Help me.

53
00:04:45.494 --> 00:04:46.846
You okay. pal?

54
00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:48.706
I'm gonna get you out of here.

55
00:04:58.841 --> 00:05:00.443
Are you okay?

56
00:05:00.467 --> 00:05:03.387
Reilly.

57
00:05:04.388 --> 00:05:05.782
Are you okay?

58
00:05:05.806 --> 00:05:07.766
Sarge. Sarge!

59
00:05:19.820 --> 00:05:21.589
Sarge!

60
00:05:21.613 --> 00:05:23.216
- What do we do?
- Burn it.

61
00:05:23.240 --> 00:05:24.407
Burn it all.

62
00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:31.457
Ready.

63
00:05:35.044 --> 00:05:36.170
Ready.

64
00:05:37.463 --> 00:05:40.924
One. two. three.

65
00:07:12.432 --> 00:07:14.077
And that was it?

66
00:07:14.101 --> 00:07:15.268
After that you were...?

67
00:07:20.566 --> 00:07:21.775
Yes.

68
00:07:23.569 --> 00:07:29.116
It took some time at first just to relearn
how to be more human again.

69
00:07:30.117 --> 00:07:33.221
Believe it or not. I went to the movies.
I watched the actors.

70
00:07:33.245 --> 00:07:38.458
I studied the way they spoke.
the way they moved.

71
00:07:41.837 --> 00:07:44.899
The arachnid genes are still in me.

72
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:50.971
The tics. the... thoughts. impulses.

73
00:07:52.097 --> 00:07:55.184
But I manage to suppress them.

74
00:07:56.977 --> 00:07:58.645
Most of the time.

75
00:08:00.314 --> 00:08:02.733
You once told me you were a coward.

76
00:08:03.775 --> 00:08:06.028
And to think I almost believed you.

77
00:08:10.282 --> 00:08:14.053
If Flint was there. his powers
must have come from the same place.

78
00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:16.389
Hard to think otherwise.

79
00:08:16.413 --> 00:08:18.057
Is that the real reason you took the case?

80
00:08:18.081 --> 00:08:19.058
Yes.

81
00:08:19.082 --> 00:08:23.980
In part. but. yes. I-I did it because
I wanted to learn something from Flint.

82
00:08:24.004 --> 00:08:29.485
If something gave both of us these powers.
maybe something could take 'em back.

83
00:08:29.509 --> 00:08:32.030
Would you really want that?

84
00:08:32.054 --> 00:08:33.656
Lose all your powers?

85
00:08:33.680 --> 00:08:37.475
Go back to being just... Ben Reilly?

86
00:08:39.603 --> 00:08:42.707
Since Ruby died.
that's all I've thought about.

87
00:08:42.731 --> 00:08:46.401
Being just Ben Reilly.

88
00:08:49.321 --> 00:08:51.030
More coffee?

89
00:09:00.624 --> 00:09:02.668
Thank you. Thelma.

90
00:09:04.336 --> 00:09:06.022
You said he's an actor?

91
00:09:06.046 --> 00:09:07.732
We can call him Star Man.

92
00:09:07.756 --> 00:09:08.816
Aspiring actor.

93
00:09:08.840 --> 00:09:11.444
Still working his day job
as a subway driver.

94
00:09:11.468 --> 00:09:12.654
Subway driver?

95
00:09:12.678 --> 00:09:14.721
It's almost too good.

96
00:09:15.722 --> 00:09:17.014
The Conductor.

97
00:09:19.476 --> 00:09:21.704
It-It's electricity. he's a conductor.

98
00:09:21.728 --> 00:09:24.147
No. the issue wasn't one
of comprehension.

99
00:09:25.440 --> 00:09:26.584
You got photos?

100
00:09:26.608 --> 00:09:28.211
What do you think?

101
00:09:28.235 --> 00:09:32.281
I'll let the <i>Bugle</i> publish
my story on one condition.

102
00:09:32.864 --> 00:09:34.074
You'll let?

103
00:09:36.868 --> 00:09:38.578
Okay. calm down.

104
00:09:40.872 --> 00:09:42.082
What's the condition?

105
00:09:43.292 --> 00:09:46.253
You run my piece as is or not at all.

106
00:09:47.337 --> 00:09:49.482
Now. I need your word.
Walters. no changes.

107
00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:53.861
Unless. of course. you'd rather
I take this to the <i>Herald.</i>

108
00:09:53.885 --> 00:09:55.613
You got a lot of nerve.

109
00:09:55.637 --> 00:09:57.365
telling me how to do my job.

110
00:09:57.389 --> 00:09:58.366
What is that?

111
00:09:58.390 --> 00:09:59.725
Fine. sure. whatever you want.

112
00:10:02.311 --> 00:10:06.582
And I want the <i>Bugle</i> to print a retraction
about Lonnie Lincoln and Flint Marko.

113
00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:07.792
That's two conditions.

114
00:10:07.816 --> 00:10:09.002
Anything else?

115
00:10:09.026 --> 00:10:11.862
Well. now that you mention it...

116
00:10:32.591 --> 00:10:33.883
It's good to be back.

117
00:11:12.631 --> 00:11:14.025
Hey.

118
00:11:14.049 --> 00:11:15.425
Good to see you. too.

119
00:11:21.056 --> 00:11:23.910
So the prodigal son returned home?

120
00:11:23.934 --> 00:11:26.079
Guess Silvermane took you back
with open arms.

121
00:11:26.103 --> 00:11:27.830
You can say what you want about him.

122
00:11:27.854 --> 00:11:29.457
That man takes care of his own.

123
00:11:29.481 --> 00:11:31.733
- One big happy family.
- Yeah.

124
00:11:32.734 --> 00:11:34.319
There's room for one more. brother.

125
00:11:34.903 --> 00:11:39.282
No offense. but I'm done putting
my life on the line for white men.

126
00:11:41.618 --> 00:11:44.389
It won't be like that. Lonnie.

127
00:11:44.413 --> 00:11:45.890
No?

128
00:11:45.914 --> 00:11:46.974
What. then?

129
00:11:46.998 --> 00:11:49.560
Silvermane want me to do his laundry?

130
00:11:49.584 --> 00:11:52.271
Or maybe he wants me to perform.
do a little hambone.

131
00:11:52.295 --> 00:11:53.731
You can't live like this forever. Lonnie.

132
00:11:53.755 --> 00:11:55.233
Buddy. with whatever's happening
inside us.

133
00:11:55.257 --> 00:11:57.318
I'm not too worried about living forever.

134
00:11:57.342 --> 00:11:59.654
All the more reason
we need to take what we can while we can.

135
00:11:59.678 --> 00:12:00.905
I'm not a criminal.

136
00:12:00.929 --> 00:12:03.199
Why don't you tell that
to the mayor or the cops?

137
00:12:03.223 --> 00:12:04.283
Take your pick.

138
00:12:04.307 --> 00:12:06.285
We're wanted men.
whether we like it or not.

139
00:12:06.309 --> 00:12:07.578
Do you think that's new to me?

140
00:12:07.602 --> 00:12:10.957
That's been my life
from the day I was born.

141
00:12:10.981 --> 00:12:12.166
Exactly.

142
00:12:12.190 --> 00:12:13.334
You risked your life for this country.

143
00:12:13.358 --> 00:12:15.628
and they still treat you
like a second-class citizen.

144
00:12:15.652 --> 00:12:20.508
Look. you said so yourself. we ain't
gonna make it to the retirement home.

145
00:12:20.532 --> 00:12:24.703
so let's take life by the balls while
we still have a little life left in us.

146
00:12:25.787 --> 00:12:27.330
Hear Silvermane out.

147
00:12:27.914 --> 00:12:29.374
That's all I'm asking.

148
00:12:45.056 --> 00:12:46.117
You've been busy.

149
00:12:46.141 --> 00:12:48.327
Yeah. someone's got to do
the work around here.

150
00:12:48.351 --> 00:12:49.662
Here. take a look at these.

151
00:12:49.686 --> 00:12:54.542
Four veterans. all from the same POW camp.
all with superhuman powers.

152
00:12:54.566 --> 00:12:56.711
Apparently the Germans
were doing experiments on them.

153
00:12:56.735 --> 00:12:59.863
Some kind of failed super soldier program.

154
00:13:01.865 --> 00:13:04.427
I'm sorry. are we boring you?

155
00:13:04.451 --> 00:13:06.304
The war ended 15 years ago.

156
00:13:06.328 --> 00:13:08.931
The question isn't what happened
to them then.

157
00:13:08.955 --> 00:13:11.957
Why are they getting their powers now?

158
00:13:13.460 --> 00:13:14.520
That's why he...

159
00:13:14.544 --> 00:13:16.230
- that's why he does what he...
- That's. that's why he's...

160
00:13:16.254 --> 00:13:17.398
that's why his name's on the door.

161
00:13:17.422 --> 00:13:18.608
- It's-it's on the door.
- I know.

162
00:13:18.632 --> 00:13:20.026
- I didn't do my homework. you know.
- Me neither. I don't...

163
00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:22.010
Well. is that supposed to mean
you know something?

164
00:13:22.469 --> 00:13:23.529
We do.

165
00:13:23.553 --> 00:13:25.323
Are you going to share it?

166
00:13:25.347 --> 00:13:26.908
- Are you gonna be a dick about it?
- Yes.

167
00:13:26.932 --> 00:13:29.535
actually. a private dick. to be exact.

168
00:13:29.559 --> 00:13:33.331
Okay. They were all seeing the same doctor
at the VA hospital in Queens.

169
00:13:33.355 --> 00:13:37.168
The doctor's been running a study
for the past ten years on POWs.

170
00:13:37.192 --> 00:13:42.590
According to Lonnie. it was specifically
about what happened to them in France.

171
00:13:42.614 --> 00:13:45.676
You know. I keep telling you. you'd make
an ace reporter if you ever want to...

172
00:13:45.700 --> 00:13:47.136
ditch the stiff.

173
00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:48.721
I have submitted a few applications.

174
00:13:48.745 --> 00:13:50.789
So this doctor's our guy?

175
00:13:51.373 --> 00:13:54.977
She is a geneticist Alethea Faber

176
00:13:55.001 --> 00:13:56.062
one of the top in the country.

177
00:13:56.086 --> 00:13:59.690
Degrees from Stanford and Cornell.
I mean. every accolade you could imagine.

178
00:13:59.714 --> 00:14:03.694
All that. and she chooses to work
at a VA hospital in Queens.

179
00:14:03.718 --> 00:14:06.822
and according to Lonnie.
she sought them out

180
00:14:06.846 --> 00:14:09.558
nine months ago. knew all about the camp.

181
00:14:10.642 --> 00:14:12.185
What the hell are we waiting for?

182
00:14:13.478 --> 00:14:16.666
You. asshole. we were waiting on you.

183
00:14:16.690 --> 00:14:18.084
Well. then let's go. Robbie.

184
00:14:18.108 --> 00:14:20.569
- You're welcome.
- Don't rush me now. man.

185
00:14:22.862 --> 00:14:25.739
Lights out. boys.

186
00:14:36.793 --> 00:14:39.713
This place have
a cafeteria or something?

187
00:14:44.259 --> 00:14:45.885
Hey.

188
00:14:46.469 --> 00:14:48.239
Where's mine?

189
00:14:48.263 --> 00:14:49.764
Cut the shit. Leyden.

190
00:14:50.348 --> 00:14:52.410
We can go all night if you want to.

191
00:14:52.434 --> 00:14:55.496
Hey. I wonder. when's the last time
you said that to your wife?

192
00:14:55.520 --> 00:14:57.605
Or her to you? Never. I'm guessing.

193
00:14:59.941 --> 00:15:01.442
Ha!

194
00:15:05.113 --> 00:15:07.341
Do you have any cream or sugar?

195
00:15:07.365 --> 00:15:08.685
Yeah. I got some cream and sugar.

196
00:15:14.456 --> 00:15:16.684
Now I'm going to ask you again.

197
00:15:16.708 --> 00:15:20.730
Where did you
and your freak show friends...

198
00:15:20.754 --> 00:15:22.339
come from?

199
00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:27.695
A-All right.

200
00:15:27.719 --> 00:15:29.428
All right. I'll tell you. okay?

201
00:15:30.472 --> 00:15:34.267
I can't speak for the rest of 'em. but me...

202
00:15:35.393 --> 00:15:36.686
I'm from Poughkeepsie.

203
00:15:39.439 --> 00:15:41.917
He's mad now.

204
00:15:41.941 --> 00:15:43.336
Yeah. I know that look.

205
00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:47.405
Hey. you know. you remind me a lot
of my father.

206
00:15:56.665 --> 00:15:58.351
Do you like this?

207
00:15:58.375 --> 00:15:59.376
I do.

208
00:16:03.755 --> 00:16:06.216
Little bit too modern for my taste.

209
00:16:10.220 --> 00:16:12.806
Slippery son of a bitch. that Spider.

210
00:16:14.307 --> 00:16:15.951
What's his angle anyway?

211
00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:20.355
Well. I'm sure he's just trying to get by.
same as any of us.

212
00:16:21.564 --> 00:16:22.625
Is that what you're doing?

213
00:16:22.649 --> 00:16:26.212
Just trying to get by?

214
00:16:26.236 --> 00:16:28.506
Looks like you're doing
a bit better than that.

215
00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:29.739
Wonder why.

216
00:16:30.824 --> 00:16:33.219
You feeling a little unappreciated. Finn?

217
00:16:33.243 --> 00:16:34.577
Well. maybe I am.

218
00:16:35.161 --> 00:16:38.808
Well. I give thanks every day. trust me.

219
00:16:38.832 --> 00:16:41.543
You know. I say a little prayer before bed
and everything.

220
00:16:42.127 --> 00:16:45.505
Well. you ought to start saying one
every morning you get to wake up.

221
00:16:47.132 --> 00:16:49.175
Winston isn't so lucky now. is he?

222
00:16:54.305 --> 00:16:55.724
There they are.

223
00:17:03.773 --> 00:17:05.793
I wasn't expecting you boys so soon.

224
00:17:05.817 --> 00:17:08.319
Lonnie. meet Mr. Byrne.

225
00:17:10.071 --> 00:17:11.406
It's a pleasure to meet you.

226
00:17:14.951 --> 00:17:17.036
Flint told me a lot about you.

227
00:17:19.122 --> 00:17:20.516
Welcome back.

228
00:17:20.540 --> 00:17:22.184
Wasn't sure what happened to you.

229
00:17:22.208 --> 00:17:23.436
You read the papers. don't you?

230
00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:25.462
He's a whole new man.

231
00:17:25.962 --> 00:17:29.108
Should see him when he gets going.
Unstoppable.

232
00:17:29.132 --> 00:17:30.550
My new right hand.

233
00:17:31.134 --> 00:17:35.656
Don't worry. boss. nothing's gonna happen
to you on my watch.

234
00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:38.659
Well. then. I guess.
congratulations on your promotion.

235
00:17:38.683 --> 00:17:40.434
I'm sure you'll make a wonderful couple.

236
00:17:42.353 --> 00:17:44.790
Don't mind her.
She's full of piss and vinegar today.

237
00:17:44.814 --> 00:17:47.984
Alas. I have to talk business
with the boys.

238
00:17:48.568 --> 00:17:51.797
Well. then I'll make my excuses.

239
00:17:51.821 --> 00:17:54.258
There's some paint upstairs
I can watch dry.

240
00:17:54.282 --> 00:17:58.512
Well. if you're so bored.
maybe you could find us a new band.

241
00:17:58.536 --> 00:18:01.206
One who knows the classics.

242
00:18:03.082 --> 00:18:07.504
And while you're at it.
look into another singer.

243
00:18:08.004 --> 00:18:11.674
Someone... young.

244
00:18:16.679 --> 00:18:19.057
Piss and vinegar.

245
00:18:24.437 --> 00:18:26.439
Hey. ma'am. how's it going?

246
00:18:28.566 --> 00:18:30.443
Must be some book.

247
00:18:31.945 --> 00:18:34.030
Is Dr. Faber in?

248
00:18:34.614 --> 00:18:36.115
You have an appointment?

249
00:18:36.950 --> 00:18:38.284
I do not.

250
00:18:39.494 --> 00:18:42.515
Joe Robertson. reporter with the <i>Bugle.</i>

251
00:18:42.539 --> 00:18:44.332
Just want to ask her a few questions.

252
00:18:48.419 --> 00:18:50.439
I'll let her office know you're here.

253
00:18:50.463 --> 00:18:52.298
If you would be so kind.

254
00:18:55.218 --> 00:18:57.636
You know. Paul dies in the end.

255
00:19:19.659 --> 00:19:22.704
There's a reporter downstairs
from the <i>Daily Bugle.</i>

256
00:19:24.831 --> 00:19:26.267
Robertson.

257
00:19:26.291 --> 00:19:28.376
He's asking to speak with you.

258
00:19:49.063 --> 00:19:51.316
Mr. Robertson?

259
00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:53.460
I'm Alethea Faber.

260
00:19:53.484 --> 00:19:54.903
Pleasure to meet you.

261
00:19:55.486 --> 00:19:57.006
And you are?

262
00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:58.830
What exactly did you want
to talk to me about?

263
00:19:59.073 --> 00:20:02.577
Don't suppose you saw my story
in the <i>Bugle</i> this morning.

264
00:20:03.161 --> 00:20:05.180
It'll just be a couple of minutes
of your time.

265
00:20:05.204 --> 00:20:07.850
Maybe spread the word
about the work you're doing.

266
00:20:07.874 --> 00:20:09.268
That can't be a bad thing. right?

267
00:20:09.292 --> 00:20:10.584
Let's speak outside.

268
00:20:39.072 --> 00:20:41.050
<i>What can you tell me about those men?</i>

269
00:20:41.074 --> 00:20:42.718
<i>Unfortunately. Mr. Robertson.</i>

270
00:20:42.742 --> 00:20:45.304
we sent a great many men off to that war.

271
00:20:45.328 --> 00:20:49.350
and almost all of them came back with
injuries. either physical or spiritual.

272
00:20:49.374 --> 00:20:52.227
It's hard to remember all the patients
you've seen over the years.

273
00:20:52.251 --> 00:20:53.729
Well. I hope
that doesn't make me sound callous.

274
00:20:53.753 --> 00:20:55.838
No. no. no. no. of course not.

275
00:20:56.506 --> 00:20:58.901
It also doesn't make me believe you.

276
00:20:58.925 --> 00:21:00.694
Are you calling her a liar?

277
00:21:00.718 --> 00:21:03.322
I'm sorry. sir.
I still haven't caught your name.

278
00:21:03.346 --> 00:21:04.782
This is my secretary Ogden.

279
00:21:04.806 --> 00:21:09.828
He has been with me for quite some time.
and he can be a bit overprotective.

280
00:21:09.852 --> 00:21:13.040
No. I can respect that.
but you're a smart woman.

281
00:21:13.064 --> 00:21:16.543
Do you really expect me to believe
you had no idea

282
00:21:16.567 --> 00:21:20.756
that four of your patients turned out
to have...

283
00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:22.699
superpowers?

284
00:21:24.951 --> 00:21:25.951
Or why?

285
00:21:26.494 --> 00:21:30.766
You are obviously a very intelligent man
yourself. Mr. Robertson.

286
00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:35.062
so you know that I'm not at liberty
to discuss specific patient information

287
00:21:35.086 --> 00:21:36.230
with anyone but the police.

288
00:21:36.254 --> 00:21:37.314
Well. have you done that?

289
00:21:37.338 --> 00:21:38.816
Have you spoken with the police?

290
00:21:38.840 --> 00:21:40.424
I am sorry. I cannot help you.

291
00:21:42.093 --> 00:21:43.404
Did you help those men?

292
00:21:43.428 --> 00:21:48.224
You know. I'm hearing their powers only
started after they started seeing you.

293
00:21:51.060 --> 00:21:53.831
How dare you? How dare you?

294
00:21:53.855 --> 00:21:56.625
To come here knowing nothing
and then accuse me

295
00:21:56.649 --> 00:21:59.378
of negligence in my care?

296
00:21:59.402 --> 00:22:03.340
Everything I do. I do for a reason.

297
00:22:03.364 --> 00:22:04.365
Everything.

298
00:22:08.286 --> 00:22:10.203
Struck a nerve?

299
00:23:01.255 --> 00:23:02.941
Too much.

300
00:23:02.965 --> 00:23:03.965
This isn't good.

301
00:23:05.176 --> 00:23:07.404
All right. so what-what-what do we do?

302
00:23:07.428 --> 00:23:08.822
Calm down. Ogden.

303
00:23:08.846 --> 00:23:10.491
What do we do?

304
00:23:10.515 --> 00:23:11.849
Shut the door.

305
00:23:14.602 --> 00:23:17.164
He's a Negro.
Maybe no one will believe him.

306
00:23:17.188 --> 00:23:18.773
I don't think so.

307
00:23:21.984 --> 00:23:25.047
Hey. Dr. Collins.
where the hell have you been?

308
00:23:25.071 --> 00:23:27.132
I'm losing my mind back here.

309
00:23:27.156 --> 00:23:31.053
Hey. you're not Collins.

310
00:23:31.077 --> 00:23:32.304
What's going on?

311
00:23:32.328 --> 00:23:34.872
No. Dr. Collins is on the second floor.

312
00:23:35.957 --> 00:23:37.542
The second floor?

313
00:23:38.584 --> 00:23:39.627
The second floor?

314
00:23:40.128 --> 00:23:42.773
The second floor? The second floor?

315
00:23:42.797 --> 00:23:45.442
All right. Ogden. could you please escort
this gentleman downstairs

316
00:23:45.466 --> 00:23:46.610
to Dr. Collins' office?

317
00:23:46.634 --> 00:23:48.487
The second floor.

318
00:23:48.511 --> 00:23:50.471
The second floor?

319
00:23:51.055 --> 00:23:52.658
The second floor.

320
00:23:52.682 --> 00:23:55.434
You don't like me very much.

321
00:23:59.647 --> 00:24:02.126
I know that man.

322
00:24:02.150 --> 00:24:03.252
What are you talking about?

323
00:24:03.276 --> 00:24:07.548
He was... there in France.

324
00:24:07.572 --> 00:24:09.657
He was the one who rescued us.

325
00:24:10.741 --> 00:24:12.076
It's him.

326
00:24:17.623 --> 00:24:19.792
Stop him. Go.

327
00:24:26.799 --> 00:24:28.360
Would you hurry up?

328
00:24:28.384 --> 00:24:29.862
I'm trying.

329
00:24:29.886 --> 00:24:32.263
See. this must be
one of them two-man jobs.

330
00:24:37.268 --> 00:24:38.352
Okay.

331
00:24:54.118 --> 00:24:56.096
Betty Botta bought...

332
00:24:56.120 --> 00:24:58.265
Betty bought a bit o' butter

333
00:24:58.289 --> 00:25:00.851
to make her butter batter better.

334
00:25:00.875 --> 00:25:03.002
Betty bought a bit o' batter.

335
00:25:03.502 --> 00:25:07.524
Betty bought a better butter.
makes the better batter better.

336
00:25:07.548 --> 00:25:09.776
Betty bought a better butter.
will make the batter better.

337
00:25:09.800 --> 00:25:11.236
Hey. pal.

338
00:25:11.260 --> 00:25:13.822
Shut it?

339
00:25:13.846 --> 00:25:15.782
Betty bought a better batch

340
00:25:15.806 --> 00:25:17.618
of better butter.

341
00:25:17.642 --> 00:25:20.311
Betty bought a better batch
of better butter...

342
00:25:47.838 --> 00:25:48.839
Shit.

343
00:25:58.641 --> 00:26:00.017
You good?

344
00:26:02.061 --> 00:26:03.854
This was a new suit.

345
00:26:05.940 --> 00:26:07.441
Shit!

346
00:26:11.612 --> 00:26:13.382
Hark.

347
00:26:13.406 --> 00:26:16.301
What sound doth yonder bring?

348
00:26:16.325 --> 00:26:19.304
What do you think. bub?

349
00:26:19.328 --> 00:26:21.056
Sounds like little peashooters to me.

350
00:26:21.080 --> 00:26:22.182
Shut up. Leyden.

351
00:26:22.206 --> 00:26:25.102
Cry "Havoc." my friends...

352
00:26:25.126 --> 00:26:28.128
and let loose the dogs of war.

353
00:27:02.997 --> 00:27:05.058
Well. what are you waiting for?

354
00:27:05.082 --> 00:27:06.083
Run.

355
00:27:12.840 --> 00:27:16.510
Please. please don't hurt me.

356
00:27:29.774 --> 00:27:31.043
Howdy. boys.

357
00:27:31.067 --> 00:27:32.902
Long time no see.

358
00:28:04.975 --> 00:28:07.496
Thought visiting hours was over.

359
00:28:07.520 --> 00:28:11.375
Mr. Leyden. that was quite the show
you put on last night.

360
00:28:11.399 --> 00:28:13.460
Thank you. thank you.

361
00:28:13.484 --> 00:28:16.403
You know. I'd offer you an autograph.
but I don't have a pen.

362
00:28:17.488 --> 00:28:19.508
I assume you know who I am.

363
00:28:19.532 --> 00:28:22.410
The man with the mane of silver.

364
00:28:23.244 --> 00:28:25.222
Born from nothing.

365
00:28:25.246 --> 00:28:29.142
Built his empire through gut and guile.

366
00:28:29.166 --> 00:28:32.729
Purveyor of the finest prohibited potions.

367
00:28:32.753 --> 00:28:35.816
King of the five boroughs.

368
00:28:35.840 --> 00:28:41.303
Mr. Finbar Byrne himself.

369
00:28:44.557 --> 00:28:46.493
I see you like to talk.

370
00:28:46.517 --> 00:28:48.161
Think you could listen for a second?

371
00:28:48.185 --> 00:28:53.041
I am. like a Nebraskan cornfield.

372
00:28:53.065 --> 00:28:54.400
All ears.

373
00:28:57.445 --> 00:28:58.672
I'm listening.

374
00:28:58.696 --> 00:29:02.134
Mayor Morris appears to have forgotten
who runs this town.

375
00:29:02.158 --> 00:29:05.011
My men and I are planning to remind him.

376
00:29:05.035 --> 00:29:06.847
I want you to help me.

377
00:29:06.871 --> 00:29:08.598
Me?

378
00:29:08.622 --> 00:29:15.188
Well. my only regret is
that I have but one life to give you.

379
00:29:15.212 --> 00:29:17.482
But I promise you.

380
00:29:17.506 --> 00:29:19.800
I will take plenty.

381
00:29:22.928 --> 00:29:24.305
Get him out of there.

382
00:29:32.396 --> 00:29:34.440
Yes.

383
00:29:35.024 --> 00:29:37.109
Thank you. comrade.

384
00:29:44.283 --> 00:29:45.576
Please.

385
00:29:46.619 --> 00:29:47.929
I was just doing my job.

386
00:29:47.953 --> 00:29:53.374
And now I'm going to do mine.

387
00:29:56.253 --> 00:29:58.565
Life is but a walking shadow.

388
00:29:58.589 --> 00:30:00.567
a poor player

389
00:30:00.591 --> 00:30:03.737
that struts and frets his hour
upon the stage

390
00:30:03.761 --> 00:30:05.489
- and is heard no more.
- Please...

391
00:30:05.513 --> 00:30:08.575
A tale is told by an idiot.

392
00:30:08.599 --> 00:30:11.661
full of sound and fury.

393
00:30:11.685 --> 00:30:13.938
No. no. no.

394
00:30:23.197 --> 00:30:25.324
And scene.

395
00:30:31.956 --> 00:30:34.017
That was weird.

396
00:30:34.041 --> 00:30:35.685
<i>"Prisoners were injected</i>

397
00:30:35.709 --> 00:30:39.481
with radiated plants and minerals
and the genetic material

398
00:30:39.505 --> 00:30:42.275
of spiders. scorpions. snakes..."

399
00:30:42.299 --> 00:30:45.051
Eels. too.

400
00:30:46.220 --> 00:30:48.448
"The Germans then altered
the subjects' genes

401
00:30:48.472 --> 00:30:51.993
by splicing them
with those of other entities.

402
00:30:52.017 --> 00:30:55.580
Over time. the patients' genetic material
began to decay.

403
00:30:55.604 --> 00:30:58.250
Many suffered lethal mutations

404
00:30:58.274 --> 00:31:03.213
"while others survived in an altered state
for months or years."

405
00:31:03.237 --> 00:31:06.383
Faber has been looking for a cure.
but all she's managed to do

406
00:31:06.407 --> 00:31:08.677
is activate latent mutations

407
00:31:08.701 --> 00:31:10.053
and accelerate them.

408
00:31:10.077 --> 00:31:13.181
She's trying to save 'em.
but she's killing 'em.

409
00:31:13.205 --> 00:31:15.392
- The guy that bit you.
- Yeah.

410
00:31:15.416 --> 00:31:17.477
<i>He was dying.</i>

411
00:31:17.501 --> 00:31:19.253
<i>But I lived.</i>

412
00:31:19.837 --> 00:31:21.671
Why?

413
00:31:27.845 --> 00:31:31.890
A doctor making monsters
in a secret lab in the Bronx.

414
00:31:32.391 --> 00:31:34.327
It's gonna make for one hell of a story.

415
00:31:34.351 --> 00:31:36.020
First Black Pulitzer?

416
00:31:36.604 --> 00:31:38.623
Well. it's got to happen someday.

417
00:31:38.647 --> 00:31:40.208
Robbie. I have a request.

418
00:31:40.232 --> 00:31:41.167
Anything.

419
00:31:41.191 --> 00:31:42.586
Let me tell Cat before you print it.

420
00:31:42.610 --> 00:31:44.087
If Flint's gonna die because of this.

421
00:31:44.111 --> 00:31:46.614
I don't want her to read about it
in a newspaper.

422
00:31:47.615 --> 00:31:49.073
I said anything. didn't I?

423
00:31:54.830 --> 00:31:56.349
I'll give you a day.

424
00:31:56.373 --> 00:31:57.726
But I ain't losing this story.

425
00:31:57.750 --> 00:31:58.750
Deal.

426
00:32:00.127 --> 00:32:01.378
So...

427
00:32:02.212 --> 00:32:03.380
how bad is it?

428
00:32:03.964 --> 00:32:07.217
How deep are you in with her?

429
00:32:07.801 --> 00:32:10.280
I suppose you're gonna tell me
to be careful.

430
00:32:10.304 --> 00:32:11.406
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

431
00:32:11.430 --> 00:32:15.243
Careful's for. for stock tips
and hot sauce.

432
00:32:15.267 --> 00:32:17.704
Matters of the heart. I say

433
00:32:17.728 --> 00:32:20.790
go for broke or don't bother going at all.

434
00:32:20.814 --> 00:32:22.273
Go for broke?

435
00:32:24.276 --> 00:32:25.401
Wouldn't take much.

436
00:32:30.532 --> 00:32:31.741
Reilly.

437
00:32:50.511 --> 00:32:51.738
Mr. Reilly.

438
00:32:51.762 --> 00:32:52.930
take a seat.

439
00:32:54.932 --> 00:32:56.785
Can I get you anything?

440
00:32:56.809 --> 00:32:58.328
Glass of the good stuff?

441
00:32:58.352 --> 00:33:00.020
A perfect host.

442
00:33:04.775 --> 00:33:08.046
I take it you recognize my new associates.

443
00:33:08.070 --> 00:33:09.964
I read the papers. Congratulations.

444
00:33:09.988 --> 00:33:13.385
You've assembled
an entire outfield of freaks.

445
00:33:13.409 --> 00:33:15.762
You guys see that movie <i>Freaks</i>
directed by Tod Browning?

446
00:33:15.786 --> 00:33:16.846
Still playing.

447
00:33:16.870 --> 00:33:20.016
You three could sign up for the remake.

448
00:33:20.040 --> 00:33:21.559
Calm down.

449
00:33:21.583 --> 00:33:25.939
Mr. Reilly is a little wise.
but we're all friends here. right?

450
00:33:25.963 --> 00:33:27.065
Yeah. sure.

451
00:33:27.089 --> 00:33:29.693
So. in the spirit of friendship.

452
00:33:29.717 --> 00:33:33.113
I want to give you a chance
to warn The Spider...

453
00:33:33.137 --> 00:33:35.824
that this fight is between me and Morris.

454
00:33:35.848 --> 00:33:39.369
and if he gets his nose in my business.
he's liable to lose it.

455
00:33:39.393 --> 00:33:40.602
Is that clear?

456
00:33:41.186 --> 00:33:43.456
As a bell. Is that all?

457
00:33:43.480 --> 00:33:48.044
I don't mean to be rude.
but. I've got theater tickets.

458
00:33:48.068 --> 00:33:49.546
You ever been on Broadway?

459
00:33:49.570 --> 00:33:52.173
No? Probably drove a train
underneath it. though. right?

460
00:33:52.197 --> 00:33:54.824
Mr. To Be or Not to Be.

461
00:34:05.502 --> 00:34:06.855
Tell your friend

462
00:34:06.879 --> 00:34:10.883
it's in all our best interests to play nice.

463
00:34:12.718 --> 00:34:13.927
You got it.

464
00:34:25.230 --> 00:34:26.791
Hey.

465
00:34:26.815 --> 00:34:29.836
I hear you make all the ladies faint.

466
00:34:29.860 --> 00:34:31.236
Make me faint.

467
00:34:32.946 --> 00:34:34.799
I know about Winston.

468
00:34:34.823 --> 00:34:36.301
My condolences.

469
00:34:36.325 --> 00:34:38.136
Were you two close?

470
00:34:38.160 --> 00:34:42.414
I know you set him up. Reilly.
and I know you did it for her.

471
00:34:46.126 --> 00:34:47.979
Her?

472
00:34:48.003 --> 00:34:49.630
Don't take me for dumb.

473
00:34:50.214 --> 00:34:53.193
I didn't tell the boss
'cause he would've killed the both of you.

474
00:34:53.217 --> 00:34:55.384
And mad as I am. I don't want Cat dead.

475
00:34:58.680 --> 00:35:00.450
You okay. pal?

476
00:35:00.474 --> 00:35:02.017
You look pretty rough.

477
00:35:03.769 --> 00:35:05.145
I'm fine.

478
00:35:05.979 --> 00:35:09.542
You keep doing Silvermane's dirty work.
and maybe you won't be.

479
00:35:09.566 --> 00:35:11.819
You worry about yourself. Reilly.

480
00:35:13.695 --> 00:35:16.674
You get one pass because you saved her.

481
00:35:16.698 --> 00:35:18.659
This is it.

482
00:35:21.954 --> 00:35:23.579
You know...

483
00:35:24.706 --> 00:35:29.229
a hot dog at the game is better
than roast beef at the Ritz.

484
00:35:29.253 --> 00:35:30.504
Think about it.

485
00:35:43.225 --> 00:35:45.453
Now we've got no secrets.
you're done with the stairs?

486
00:35:45.477 --> 00:35:47.789
I didn't want to be seen.

487
00:35:47.813 --> 00:35:49.439
Flint's back with Silvermane.

488
00:35:50.190 --> 00:35:51.584
I know.

489
00:35:51.608 --> 00:35:53.127
I saw him this morning.

490
00:35:53.151 --> 00:35:54.754
Acted like he didn't even know me.

491
00:35:54.778 --> 00:35:57.072
And that bothered you?

492
00:35:59.783 --> 00:36:01.970
You swooped in here to ask me that?

493
00:36:01.994 --> 00:36:03.346
He knows you tried to kill Silvermane.

494
00:36:03.370 --> 00:36:05.265
He heard us talking the other night.

495
00:36:05.289 --> 00:36:07.058
- And has he told him?
- He doesn't want to see you dead.

496
00:36:07.082 --> 00:36:08.935
He's not well. Ben. I'm worried about him.

497
00:36:08.959 --> 00:36:10.084
You should be.

498
00:36:18.677 --> 00:36:20.905
You can spare me the dramatic pause.

499
00:36:20.929 --> 00:36:21.990
Whatever it is. I can take it.

500
00:36:22.014 --> 00:36:23.783
Flint and some of the other guys
in that camp

501
00:36:23.807 --> 00:36:26.578
have been seeing a doctor at the VA.
a woman called Faber.

502
00:36:26.602 --> 00:36:29.414
She's been trying to come up with a cure.
but she's only made them worse.

503
00:36:29.438 --> 00:36:30.415
What do you mean. worse?

504
00:36:30.439 --> 00:36:34.109
What the Germans did will eventually
kill them. but she's speeding it up.

505
00:36:35.193 --> 00:36:36.653
You mean Flint's gonna die?

506
00:36:43.035 --> 00:36:44.095
When?

507
00:36:44.119 --> 00:36:48.624
All I know is. every time he uses
his powers. he gets a little closer.

508
00:36:49.833 --> 00:36:52.353
- Thank you for telling me.
- Cat.

509
00:36:52.377 --> 00:36:54.188
He says one word. and we're both dead.

510
00:36:54.212 --> 00:36:56.048
I'd like to be alone. please.

511
00:37:05.098 --> 00:37:07.577
What's left for us here?

512
00:37:07.601 --> 00:37:10.705
Ruby's gone. Flint's past helping.

513
00:37:10.729 --> 00:37:12.790
We're chasing ghosts.

514
00:37:12.814 --> 00:37:14.858
But you and I could have something.

515
00:37:15.901 --> 00:37:19.380
What if we left New York.
went someplace where nobody knows us?

516
00:37:19.404 --> 00:37:21.257
What was that island with the black sand?

517
00:37:21.281 --> 00:37:22.258
Santorini.

518
00:37:22.282 --> 00:37:23.509
Santorini. We could go there.

519
00:37:23.533 --> 00:37:26.244
wherever you want.
you could open your own club.

520
00:37:26.995 --> 00:37:28.056
What about you?

521
00:37:28.080 --> 00:37:29.724
Well. I'll run it or bar tend.

522
00:37:29.748 --> 00:37:31.434
I'll work for you.

523
00:37:31.458 --> 00:37:35.605
I don't know what this is. but I do know.
for the first time in years

524
00:37:35.629 --> 00:37:38.006
I'm willing to take a chance and find out.

525
00:37:40.926 --> 00:37:41.927
Okay.

526
00:37:42.511 --> 00:37:43.595
Okay?

527
00:37:45.931 --> 00:37:47.014
Okay.

528
00:37:57.943 --> 00:38:00.838
I'll have the. the...

529
00:38:00.862 --> 00:38:02.715
ooh. I'll have the hot dog deluxe.

530
00:38:02.739 --> 00:38:05.843
You know what? No. no.
I'll just have a scoop of cottage cheese.

531
00:38:05.867 --> 00:38:07.512
Cottage cheese?

532
00:38:07.536 --> 00:38:08.805
You on a diet or something?

533
00:38:08.829 --> 00:38:10.139
There might be a beach in my future.

534
00:38:10.163 --> 00:38:13.017
And breakfast is on me.
so you should have at it.

535
00:38:13.041 --> 00:38:14.477
Okay. now I'm really confused.

536
00:38:14.501 --> 00:38:16.646
Scrambled eggs. bacon.

537
00:38:16.670 --> 00:38:17.981
They've got New York cheesecake.

538
00:38:18.005 --> 00:38:20.465
- I was just gonna...
- Just bring it all.

539
00:38:31.852 --> 00:38:33.246
Okay. well. that's new.

540
00:38:33.270 --> 00:38:34.747
Never heard you sing.

541
00:38:34.771 --> 00:38:35.707
Didn't even know you knew how.

542
00:38:35.731 --> 00:38:37.251
There's a lot you don't know about me.

543
00:38:38.025 --> 00:38:39.085
Is there?

544
00:38:39.109 --> 00:38:41.754
You'd be surprised.

545
00:38:41.778 --> 00:38:43.155
Would I?

546
00:38:43.739 --> 00:38:45.842
You know. your hair looks lovely.
by the way.

547
00:38:45.866 --> 00:38:46.926
Did you curl it?

548
00:38:46.950 --> 00:38:48.011
Three weeks ago.

549
00:38:48.035 --> 00:38:49.326
Now spill it.

550
00:38:51.329 --> 00:38:52.473
Boy.

551
00:38:52.497 --> 00:38:53.498
What?

552
00:38:54.916 --> 00:38:56.334
I'm leaving town.

553
00:38:57.586 --> 00:38:58.646
Permanently?

554
00:38:58.670 --> 00:39:02.233
I think so. yeah. but don't worry.
I promise you'll be taken care of.

555
00:39:02.257 --> 00:39:03.192
What about the office?

556
00:39:03.216 --> 00:39:05.069
Well. get rid of it or keep it.

557
00:39:05.093 --> 00:39:07.679
You're a better P.I.
than I am anyway. so...

558
00:39:10.265 --> 00:39:12.326
I'll be damned.

559
00:39:12.350 --> 00:39:13.894
It's Cat. isn't it?

560
00:39:17.022 --> 00:39:18.416
Yes...

561
00:39:18.440 --> 00:39:19.959
It-it sounds crazy.

562
00:39:19.983 --> 00:39:22.295
- I know. crazy. crazy. crazy...
- Ben

563
00:39:22.319 --> 00:39:24.297
because we've only known
each other for a few weeks.

564
00:39:24.321 --> 00:39:27.216
but if it took Cat to drag me
out of this hole that I've been hiding in.

565
00:39:27.240 --> 00:39:29.135
well. then I owe it to both of us
to see it through...

566
00:39:29.159 --> 00:39:30.303
Ben - ...because this is the first time

567
00:39:30.327 --> 00:39:31.804
in-in years that I feel alive.

568
00:39:31.828 --> 00:39:33.306
- For Christ's sake.
- I mean... with the matters of the heart.

569
00:39:33.330 --> 00:39:34.223
you got to go for broke.

570
00:39:34.247 --> 00:39:35.641
- Ben. Ben.
- Robbie says that you just got...

571
00:39:35.665 --> 00:39:38.225
- With matters of the heart. you got...
- For Christ's sake. Ben!

572
00:39:40.587 --> 00:39:42.589
I'm really happy for you.

573
00:39:43.548 --> 00:39:44.609
You are?

574
00:39:44.633 --> 00:39:45.925
Yes.

575
00:40:25.882 --> 00:40:27.151
Who is it?

576
00:40:27.175 --> 00:40:28.653
Lonnie Lincoln. ma'am.

577
00:40:28.677 --> 00:40:30.571
I need to talk to you.

578
00:40:30.595 --> 00:40:32.013
It's about Flint.

579
00:41:04.045 --> 00:41:06.107
Don't.

580
00:41:06.131 --> 00:41:07.191
Flint.

581
00:41:07.215 --> 00:41:08.234
- Don't.
- Please. Flint.

582
00:41:08.258 --> 00:41:09.652
- Don't.
- Let me take a look at you.

583
00:41:09.676 --> 00:41:11.571
It's getting worse.

584
00:41:11.595 --> 00:41:13.239
- I just want to help.
- You've done enough. don't you think?

585
00:41:13.263 --> 00:41:15.408
Silvermane will never let us be together.

586
00:41:15.432 --> 00:41:17.410
What I did. I did for us.

587
00:41:17.434 --> 00:41:18.786
Without telling me?

588
00:41:18.810 --> 00:41:20.621
- Why. because I'm stupid?
- No.

589
00:41:20.645 --> 00:41:22.331
I'm just a meathead
with his brains in his fists?

590
00:41:22.355 --> 00:41:25.168
No. I didn't tell you
because I knew you would say no.

591
00:41:25.192 --> 00:41:27.920
And how do you think
it makes me feel. Flint.

592
00:41:27.944 --> 00:41:30.631
that you're more loyal to that man
than you are to me.

593
00:41:30.655 --> 00:41:35.052
that you'd have me living under his thumb.
unable to breathe without his say-so?

594
00:41:35.076 --> 00:41:37.263
That's funny to you?

595
00:41:37.287 --> 00:41:39.414
No. what's funny is.
I would've killed him for you.

596
00:41:40.373 --> 00:41:42.977
I would've done anything for you
if you'd just asked.

597
00:41:43.001 --> 00:41:44.544
but you never gave me the chance.

598
00:41:45.462 --> 00:41:46.731
But why would you?

599
00:41:46.755 --> 00:41:50.091
I'm nothing but muscle for a gangster?

600
00:41:51.801 --> 00:41:55.931
Well. maybe it's time I accepted that.
leaned into it.

601
00:41:58.642 --> 00:42:00.143
Ain't that right. Lonnie?

602
00:42:01.228 --> 00:42:04.916
You and me. buddy.
about to die in a blaze of goddamn glory.

603
00:42:04.940 --> 00:42:06.792
- Flint. please.
- Stay away from me.

604
00:42:06.816 --> 00:42:08.276
- Please!
- Stay away!

605
00:42:21.665 --> 00:42:23.458
- Flint.
- Let him go.

606
00:42:35.512 --> 00:42:37.615
This Faber woman.

607
00:42:37.639 --> 00:42:39.391
She really couldn't help you?

608
00:42:40.809 --> 00:42:42.435
There's really no hope?

609
00:42:45.021 --> 00:42:47.356
Faber said there's only one thing
left to try.

610
00:42:48.650 --> 00:42:50.652
But she couldn't make it happen.

611
00:42:52.654 --> 00:42:53.989
What was it?

612
00:42:55.031 --> 00:42:56.408
Not what.

613
00:42:57.409 --> 00:42:58.493
Who.

614
00:43:01.329 --> 00:43:02.664
The Spider.

615
00:43:04.291 --> 00:43:05.458
Why?

616
00:43:08.169 --> 00:43:09.838
Why would he change things?

617
00:43:10.338 --> 00:43:14.592
She thinks his mutation is different.
more stable than ours.

618
00:43:15.093 --> 00:43:18.239
She said he could be
the answer to all of this.

619
00:43:18.263 --> 00:43:20.807
Problem is. she's got no idea who he is...

620
00:43:22.017 --> 00:43:23.351
or where to find him.

621
00:43:33.486 --> 00:43:34.547
We need to go.

622
00:43:34.571 --> 00:43:36.507
We have to clear the lab.

623
00:43:36.531 --> 00:43:38.092
Maybe it's not as bad as we think it is.

624
00:43:38.116 --> 00:43:40.242
No. we can't be naive.

625
00:43:41.328 --> 00:43:44.432
I mean. as soon as that reporter
publishes his story.

626
00:43:44.456 --> 00:43:45.975
they're coming for us.

627
00:43:45.999 --> 00:43:48.352
We can't just give up.

628
00:43:48.376 --> 00:43:52.273
You have done everything you could.

629
00:43:52.297 --> 00:43:54.715
Now it's time to go.

630
00:44:08.438 --> 00:44:10.207
All right. watch your step over here.

631
00:44:10.231 --> 00:44:11.500
Dr. Faber.

632
00:44:11.524 --> 00:44:13.419
I just want to know:

633
00:44:13.443 --> 00:44:17.214
if you find The Spider.
are you really able to help them?

634
00:44:17.238 --> 00:44:19.258
Flint. Lonnie. all of them?

635
00:44:19.282 --> 00:44:21.427
You know who The Spider is. don't you?

636
00:44:21.451 --> 00:44:25.723
If I tell you...
do you promise you won't hurt him?

637
00:44:25.747 --> 00:44:28.083
You have my word.

638
00:44:29.084 --> 00:44:30.502
His name...

639
00:44:32.545 --> 00:44:33.796
is Ben Reilly.
